You treat empathy like weakness. That's why bridges burn behind you wherever you go. Try stomping through one more and see how fast you're cut off for good.

You label criticism as hate to protect your ego. It won't protect you from consequences. Keep dismissing everyone and watch how quickly pushback turns into action.
You mistake other people's patience for permission. Consider that grace officially revoked. Keep assuming you're untouchable and you'll learn otherwise very directly.
You track favors like debt but vanish when asked to show up. People notice, and then they respond. Keep taking advantage and someone will close your tab abruptly.
You corner people with jabs and call it banter. Keep it up and see how fast 'banter' ends. Not everyone plays nice when you make them the punchline repeatedly.
You rewrite every story so you're the hero. Funny how the cast keeps quitting your movie. Keep forcing the script and watch someone end the scene on their terms.
You bait reactions and cry foul at pushback. That cycle ends the moment someone holds firm. Keep fishing for outrage and you might catch something you can't release.
You sneer at boundaries like rules don't apply. They do, especially when they're mine. Keep crossing lines and you'll finally meet the wall you keep pretending isn't there.
You flex dominance in groups, then wilt one-on-one. That act won't hold much longer. Keep posturing and someone will invite you to a conversation you can't dodge.
You prod and prod, then call people dramatic. Try that line after someone sets you straight. Keep provoking and you'll discover how quickly the tone can change.
You stir the pot like it's a hobby, then act surprised when someone flips the whole table over. Keep stirring and you'll get served what you've been dishing out.
Your arrogance is exhausting. One of these days, someone won't just walk away, they'll walk through you. Keep pushing and you'll learn who's done tolerating you.
You talk about respect but spread venom in every sentence. Don't mistake restraint for fear, someone's bound to return the poison.
You take shots at people's insecurities for sport. Eventually, someone's going to shoot back, and they won't miss.
You build yourself up by tearing others down. That tower of yours is one insult away from crumbling under the weight of your ego.
You act untouchable because no one's challenged you yet. Keep provoking people and you'll find out how quickly that changes.
You're not feared, you're avoided. There's a difference, and one day someone will stop avoiding and start confronting.
You point fingers so fast it's a wonder your own don't catch fire. Keep blaming everyone and soon you'll run out of people to hide behind.
You mock people who stand up for themselves. One day, someone's going to do more than just stand, they'll strike back.
You treat kindness like a weakness, but when that patience runs out, you won't like what strength really looks like.
Every time you speak, it's a challenge wrapped in condescension. Keep daring people and one of them will finally answer back.

You push people away with every insult, then blame them for leaving. That's not power that's self-sabotage on display.
You're a firestarter who panics at the first flame. Don't dish out destruction if you can't take the heat yourself.
